        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2710812561" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4210665489752809556"><b>A simply dreadful story about Mr and Mrs Twit.</b><br/> <br/>They play pranks on each other; such as worms in food, frogs in beds, psychological torture, and air space incursions.<br/>They catch and cook all types of British birds without checking to see if any are nearly extinct.<br/>They try to catch, cook and eat young boys.<br/>They force a family of monkeys to perform horrible tricks that endanger the monkeys&apos; health.<br/>They buy shotguns without a license, and intend to shoot inside a suburb.<br/><br/>That is what a politically cor</span>
  <span id="freeText4210665489752809556" style="display:none"><b>A simply dreadful story about Mr and Mrs Twit.</b><br /> <br />They play pranks on each other; such as worms in food, frogs in beds, psychological torture, and air space incursions.<br />They catch and cook all types of British birds without checking to see if any are nearly extinct.<br />They try to catch, cook and eat young boys.<br />They force a family of monkeys to perform horrible tricks that endanger the monkeys' health.<br />They buy shotguns without a license, and intend to shoot inside a suburb.<br /><br />That is what a politically correct reviewer from the nanny state would say before banning the book. But not children!<br /><br />I have read this story to many of my junior classes, who simply adored the antics of the Twits and the monkeys' revenge.<br /><br /><i>Don't tell the nanny state inspectors, but this story is Horribly Funny.</i><br /><br />Enjoy!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4210665489752809556" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
